================================================================================
THIRD-PARTY ATTRIBUTIONS
================================================================================

This starter repository describes and integrates ideas from the following
external works. The starter contains no verbatim copies of those works; their
ideas are paraphrased and cited. Anyone reusing or extending the starter is
expected to preserve attribution to the original authors below.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Legible Architecture / WYSIWID Pattern
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Eagon Meng and Daniel Jackson, "What You See Is What It Does: A Structural
Pattern for Legible Software." Onward! 2025 (ACM SPLASH).
DOI: 10.1145/3759429.3762628
arXiv: 2508.14511

The original paper is distributed under CC BY-NC 4.0. The summaries of
"concepts," "synchronizations," "flow tokens," and the bootstrap "Web concept"
that appear in `methodology/architecture/` are paraphrases written for this
project; they are not derivative copies of the paper's prose. Implementations
that follow the WYSIWID pattern should cite the paper.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Interpretable Context Methodology (ICM)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Jake Van Clief, "Interpretable Context Methodology (ICM)." 2026.
Repository: https://github.com/RinDig/Interpretable-Context-Methodology-ICM-
arXiv: 2603.16021

ICM is licensed under the MIT License. The five-layer context hierarchy, the
numbered-stage workspace pattern, and the `CONTEXT.md` stage-contract format
used throughout `features/` and the templates in `templates/stage-CONTEXT.md`
are adapted from ICM. Workspaces and features that follow this scaffold should
cite ICM.

